article.headline: Crawford 5-for-7 from 3-point range
article.linkText: Crawford's career-high 42 lifts Bulls to win
article.story:
CHICAGO (AP) -- Jamal Crawford isn't trying to rush things anymore, and he's already reaping the benefits of picking his spots. Crawford made five 3-pointers and scored a career-high 42 points in the Chicago Bulls' 100-86 victory over the Washington Wizards on Saturday night. Coming off a 30-point performance at Cleveland on Friday, Crawford outdid himself. He was 16-for-27 from the floor and 5-for-7 from 3-point range. Prior to Friday, Crawford shot just 14-for-54 in the previous three games. "I think I am being more patient, usually when you come out and rush to score it doesn't happen for you," Crawford said. "I think I'm picking my spots a lot better." Chicago started to pull away late in the third quarter, using a 12-2 run to turn a 61-60 deficit into a nine-point lead. Crawford scored nine of Chicago's 12 points. After a series of bad shooting games, Crawford wasn't ready to stop looking for his shot. "I knew I couldn't miss forever. I shot so bad, I guess I was due," he said. Crawford hit a jumper to give the Bulls a 71-63 lead at the end of the third quarter, then extended Chicago's lead with a 3-pointer to make it 82-64. Larry Hughes had 22 points for Washington and Etan Thomas added 10. Washington has dropped four straight and 12 of 15. "Twelve guys didn't perform. We didn't get it done," Hughes said. "When we play together, we play good basketball. We have to stop all the laughing and joking. This (stuff) isn't funny. Guys have to start taking it personal." Washington forward Kwame Brown was upset with Wizards head coach Eddie Jordan's strategy. "I thought he was going to sub me in to guard Antonio Davis. If a guy's posting up against a guy and he's scoring, I want to be the guy to guard him," Brown said. "I thought I should have been in there guarding Antonio when he got going." Davis finished with 11 points and nine rebounds. Crawford scored 18 first-half points for the Bulls. He hit his first four shots and was 3-for-3 from 3-point range in the first half. Crawford put Chicago ahead 43-34 on a three-point play with 4:29 left in the second quarter, but the Wizards answered with a 11-4 run, cutting the Bulls' lead to 47-45.

Game notes
Bulls center Eddy Curry hopes to be back Monday night against the Miami Heat. Curry went on the injured list Dec. 16 with a bone bruise on his left knee. "I'm hoping Monday. Right now, how I'm feeling, I definitely think I'll be up for playing on Monday," said Curry. ... Rapper Nelly attended the game. ... Hughes has led the Wizards in scoring in six consecutive games. ... Chicago has won two straight for the second time this season. ... Crawford's 42 points is the most by a Bulls player since Jalen Rose scored 44 at Houston on Mar. 16, 2002.
